{#
  Static PersistentVolume and PersistentVolumeClaim for the Immich photo
  library, backed by the homelab NFS share. Applied directly by immich.yml
  before ArgoCD syncs the Helm release. The PVC is pre-created so the Immich
  Helm chart can reference it via existingClaim without managing its lifecycle.

  The storageClassName is set to '' and volumeName is set explicitly to force
  binding to this specific PV and prevent the default StorageClass from
  interfering.

  NFS supports ReadWriteMany, allowing the Immich server and microservices
  pods to mount the library simultaneously.

  Variables:
    immich_namespace:         Kubernetes namespace where Immich is deployed.
    immich_library_nfs_size:  Nominal size annotation for the PV and PVC.
                              NFS does not enforce quotas via PVC size.
    nfs_server_ip:            IP address of the NFS server.
    immich_library_nfs_path:  Absolute path on the NFS server for the Immich
                              library (e.g. /srv/nfs/data/kubernetes/immich).

  Mount options:
    soft       Instructs the kernel to return EIO after the timeout rather than
               retrying indefinitely. Allows Kubernetes to restart the pod and
               recover automatically once the NFS server is reachable, rather
               than hanging in uninterruptible D state.
    timeo=600  Initial RPC timeout in tenths of a second (60 seconds) before
               returning EIO to the calling process under soft mount semantics.
#}
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolume
metadata:
  name: immich-library
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: immich
spec:
  capacity:
    storage: '{{ immich_library_nfs_size }}'
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  persistentVolumeReclaimPolicy: Retain
  storageClassName: ''
  mountOptions:
    - soft
    - timeo=600
  nfs:
    server: '{{ nfs_server_ip }}'
    path: '{{ immich_library_nfs_path }}'
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: immich-library
  namespace: '{{ immich_namespace }}'
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: immich
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  storageClassName: ''
  volumeName: immich-library
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: '{{ immich_library_nfs_size }}'
